1. PATCH() Function:
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ðŸ‘‰ The PATCH() Function is used to create a record, update a record in a data source.
âœ… Syntax: Patch(DataSource, Defaults(DataSource), { Column1: Value1, Column2: Value2, Column3: Value3 })
ðŸ’› Syntax: Patch(Employees, Defaults(Employees), { Name: "Manoj", Age: 25, Department: "IT" })

ðŸ‘‰ If I want to update only specific fields of a record without affecting other data, Patch() is the best choice.
âœ… For example: If you want to update a specific employee whose name is "John Doe":-
ðŸ’› Syntax: Patch(Employees, LookUp(Employees, Name = "Manoj"),{Age: 20, Department: "HR"})
